The rapid spread of the coronavirus requires better capabilities and aggressive bulk testing. JOHANNESBURG - The World Health Organization is concerned about the rapid infection rate and global spread of COVID-19. Cases have now reached 205 countries and territories, with more than 900,000 infections and nearly 50,000 deaths.  The WHO says it is working together with the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund back debt relief to help poorer nations cope with the pandemic’s social and economic consequences. READ: The world before this coronavirus and after cannot be the same "As we enter the fourth month since the start of the COVID-19 pandemic, I'm deeply concerned about the rapid escalation and global spread of infection. "Over the past five weeks, we have witnessed a near exponential growth in the number of new cases, reaching almost every country, territory and area," said WHO director-general Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus. - Map courtesy Johns Hopkins Center for Systems Science and Engineering - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.